Description

the SEN input is an internally pulled up (to 3.3V via a 5K resistor) digital input capable of measuring time difference as well as analog level signals. When an input voltage goes from 0V to 3.3V , it is known as a rising edge. The opposite is called a falling edge.


The rising edge timer is used to measure intervals between multiple rising edges.


For the rod pendulum, which oscillates between a phototransistor and an LED, we measure time between a rising edge(Rod interrupts the beam), and the next to next rising edge when the oscillation cycle is complete. The edge in the middle is skipped because the rod is returning to its original position, and only half the cycle is complete.


Gravity for a physical pendulum is calculated as ﻿8∗pi2∗rodlength/t28*pi^2*rodlength/t^28∗pi​2​​∗rodlength/t​2​​﻿ /3
